flow.descriptionCdata:
61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.0b0fa5c4-07a3-4cfb-b8d3-1dfc130ac776.prompt=Protocol\: 61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.18b678e0-ec61-45de-a1e2-8df4787c54ba.description=
Get the netstat information from a system running Freebsd prior to version 8.0
61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.32db3f88-1953-4885-8e7c-993a787af967.prompt=Username\: 61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.406e0e28-e273-42c8-9c64-ef9bfa5e1519.prompt=PrivateKeyFile\: 61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.464c506b-9eb8-40fc-bf5b-33e53e756d69.prompt=Host\: 61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.6e28e73c-7dbd-4630-821c-e554e1351afd.description=
Test whether the major version of FreeBSD we're running against is 7 or below. 
Starting with FreeBSD 8 there is a new field in the output of netstat -dbI for
the number of dropped input packets, so we have to parse the results 
differently for version 8 onward.
61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.7c2bcbc2-0a36-43f1-aaec-1211c43aff3e.prompt=Interface to query\: 61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.80b6f6f4-0d7f-486a-90ff-43431b43d56c.prompt=Password\: 61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.8230495e-8bbf-4104-bf1e-7fa2ce885c91.prompt=Name\: 61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.838c48e8-6b78-4a15-8a51-26ed2e3e9c03.prompt=Username\: 61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.90fb436e-93d1-4710-b6bd-6d7901f583a3.description=
This gets the operating system name.

Inputs\:
host -  the system to check
username - the user to log into this system as
password - the password to log in with
port - port number for connecting to the host
protocol - the protocol used to run the command (can be one of ssh, ROSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, local or WMI)
timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete
pty - (true, false) whether to use pty
privateKeyFile - The absolute path to the private key file for remote host.
sasHost - the host we want to run the ROSH command on
sasHostUsername - the username used to run the ROSH command on sasHost
usernamePrompt - the prompt that when seen should send the username
passwordPrompt - the prompt that when given should send the password

Responses\:
success - the data was obtained
failure - the data could not be obtained

Result\:
the OS name (uname return information)

Extra Results\:
returnResult -the OS name (uname return information)
61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.96f6a895-6409-4d1f-a581-6bffa6077410.prompt=Port\: 61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.9735a9b4-e2f0-40cc-80cd-ce3ef6072618.description= stdOut - STDOUT from ifconfig flags - flags parsed from ifconfig metric - metric parsed from ifconfig mtu - mtu parsed from ifconfig options - options parsed from ifconfig macAddress - MAC address parsed from ifconfig inetAddress - inet address parsed from ifconfig inetNetmask - inet netmask parsed from ifconfig inetBroadcast - inet broadcast parsed from ifconfig inet6Address - inet6 address parsed from ifconfig inet6PrefixLen - inet6 prefixlen parsed from ifconfig inet6ScopeId - inet6 scopeid parsed from ifconfig media - media parsed from ifconfig status - status parsed from ifconfig 61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.description=
This retrieves link level network metrics for an interface using netstat.  

Inputs\:
host -  the system to check
name - name of the network interface to check
addressFamily - The address family to gather information for (inet for IPv4 or inet6 for IPv6), default\: inet
username - the user to log into this system as
password - the password to log in with
privateKeyFile - The absolute path to the private key file for remote host.
port - port number for connecting to the host
protocol - the protocol used to run the command (can be one of ssh, ROSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, local or WMI)
timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete


Responses\:
success - the data was obtained
failure - the data could not be obtained

Result\:
The netstat return code

Extra Results\:
stdOut - the standard output
collisions - the collision count
ipAddress - the IP adress 
macAaddress - the MAC adress
receiveBytes - number of received bytes
receiveDrops - number of received drops
receiveErrors - number of received errors
receiveFrameErrors - synonym for receivedErrors
receivePackets - number of received packets
transmitBytes - number of transmitted bytes
transmitCarrierErrors - synonym for transmitErrors
transmitDrops - synonym for drops
transmitErrors - number of transmitted errors
transmitPackets - number of transmitted packets
drops - number of drops
receiveDrops - number of received packets which were dropped. (Only availble from systems running FreeBSD 8.0 or newer)
61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.f30ee829-59b4-422c-8ef9-0b501cdb729e.prompt=Timeout\: 61fa6d1b-88c8-4fc6-96e0-d0f5f24718bd.fb04bcb3-f9e0-413c-90b1-ea33c7e5f7f0.description=

Get the netstat information from a system running Freebsd version 8.0 or later.
